   Leading the Way to Salmon Recovery

                              [ushathumbnail.JPG]
   The challenges faced by the Northwest Fisheries Science Center are
   myriad - insufficient funding, the wildcard of global climate change
   and lawsuits. Director Usha Varanasi
   says the agency's scientists carrying out large-scale salmon recovery
   experiments need fortitude and endurance, strengths that have helped
   her in life and in her career.


   Full story -- .pdf (66Kb - requires Adobe Reader 4.0 or newer. Download
   here.)
   HTML

   For more information on Dr. Varanasi, please link to the following
   interview conducted by Women in Technology International.

